member.remarks:
The following is an example on how to call this method by passing
in the object with the event declarations, and the event name to
trigger.


   OWork work = TablesLogic.tWork.Load(workId);
   work.SupervisorID = userID;

   // The work must be saved before the TriggerWorkflowEvent
   // method is called.
   //
   work.Save();
   work.TriggerWorkflowEvent("SubmitForApproval");

member.summary:
Gets a one-to-many list of OScheduledWorkStaggeredLocation objects 
that represents information about how the works for the location
will be staggered. This is applicable only if IsStaggered = 1;

This is the Reports class that will be used by the Report Builder to call methods within this class.
All reports/dashboards that are to be exposed to the Report Builder at the Web Application layer must declare one of the following prototypes:
public static DataTable ReportMethodName(ReportParameters parameters);
public static DataSet ReportMethodName(ReportParameters parameters);

This is the Reports class that will be used by the Report Builder to call methods within this class.
All reports/dashboards that are to be exposed to the Report Builder at the Web Application layer must declare one of the following prototypes:
public static DataTable ReportMethodName(ReportParameters parameters);
public static DataSet ReportMethodName(ReportParameters parameters);

            [Column] Gets or sets a flag indicating the
            type of the store items will be transferred from:





0 - Physical Store; 

1 - Issue Location;

            [Column] Gets or sets a flag indicating the
            type of the store items will be transferred to:





0 - Physical Store; 

1 - Issue Location;

            [Column] Gets or sets a flag indicating where
            this message template is used.


0 - General; 

1 - Notify Assigned Workflow Recipients;

            [Column] Gets or sets a flag indicating the type
            of this invoice.


0 - Direct Invoice; 

1 - Matched to Purchase Order; 

2 - Matched to Purchase Order Receipt;

            [Column] Gets or sets a flag indicating if this invoice
            is a standard invoice, a credit memo, or a debit memo.




0 - Standard invoice; 

1 - Credit memo; 

2 - Debit memo;

[Column] Gets or sets a flag indicating whether the readings registered by this point always increases over time (like a water meter, electricity meter).
0 - Absolute reading for temperature sensors, vibration sensors, etc;
1 - Increasing reading for electrical meters, water meters, etc;

